But first, societies need to listen.
Indigenous societies, on the other hand, are based on worldviews where human needs are balanced with the needs of other life forms.
As Indigenous peoples, we have always understood that ecocide—the killing of an ecosystem—is commensurate with genocide.
Indigenous knowledge involves the application of particular knowledge in particular contexts.
And the sooner the better, because as scientists tell us, this will not be the last—or the worst—pandemic we are likely to see.